Messages: 101 is is the atomic number of mendelevium, an actinide.
101 is the number of the first check for new checking account in the US.
101 is is the number of floors of Taipei 101, the tallest skyscraper in the world from 2004 to 2010.
101 is the HTTP status code indicating that a client should switch protocols.
101 is the temperature in Fahrenheit of milk when it leaves the body of a cow.
101 is the number of the Vault that is the starting area of Fallout 3.
101 is the number identifying number of several infantry units in various militaries across the world, such as the American and Israeli paratrooper brigades.
101 is a number used to define the number of keys on a computer keyboard.
